entials (inflows$-$outflows) show\nstatistically valid higher values for regions in tidally perturbed galaxies.\nThese differentials, and the metal fractions from the population synthesis,\nsuggest dominant gas inflows in these galaxies. This dominance, and the\ndifferences in SF through time, confirm the previously reported effects of\ntidal interactions on SF.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Sep 2021 05:47:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-29"}
